                    <msItem n="1" xml:id="Wellcome_Ethiopian_9_1">
                        <locus from="1" to="25">Column 1, lines 1-25</locus>
                        <author key="">Anonymous</author>
                        <title key="" type="desc">Prayer for undoing charms and for protection against the evil eye of barya and legewon.</title>
                        
                        <incipit><locus>Column 1, line 1</locus>: <!-- Ge'ez text to be picked up in late-stage editing-->
                        </incipit>
                        
                        <note>According to Strelcyn, barya are a people believed to serve the demon or spirit provoking epilepsy and therefore barya is identified with this disease. Legewon is a name for Satan, chief of the barya and 
                            one of the most frequently occurring devils in Ethiopic magical literature (<ref>Strelcyn</ref>).</note>
                    </msItem>

